cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper discusses an attack on Direct-Sequence Spread Spectrum (DSSS) systems, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and cognitive radio (cs.CR). The attack also involves communication channels, which could be classified under networked systems (cs.NI) and cyber-physical systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper proposes methods to improve error-performance under the attack, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM) in terms of signal processing and error correction.
